Prerequisites
To install all the necessary tools on a Debian-based system (like Ubuntu or Kali Linux), run this command in your terminal:

Bash

sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y nmap curl gobuster subfinder figlet lolcat
Installation
To download the project from GitHub, use the following command. Remember to replace your-username with your actual GitHub username.

Bash

git clone https://github.com/your-username/DragonHunter.git
Once the cloning is complete, navigate into the project directory:

Bash

cd DragonHunter
Next, you need to make the script executable. This gives you permission to run it directly from your terminal.

Bash

chmod +x dragonhunter.sh
üê≤ Usage
To run the DragonHunter script, simply provide the target URL as an argument.

Bash

./dragonhunter.sh <target_url>
Example:

Bash

./dragonhunter.sh https://example.com
